metadata.name: Glomularus #129
metadata.description:
Glomularus is an exploration in generative, artificial life forms. The project is an extension of my Protobyte series, begun in 2004.

Driven by Verlet icosahedra and responsive tendrils, Glomulari live in a spherical virtual ecosystem (V-eco) enhanced through user interaction.

Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
  drag -> camera rotation
  drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
  scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
  1-9: add acceleration
  -, +: reduce | increase V-eco sphere radius
  f, g: reduce | increase fog
  p: screen capture

Tip:
To decrease creature acceleration, reduce V-eco sphere radius

Note:
Please post your favorite Glomularus screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

metadata.name: Saccharine Biomes: Hills #138
metadata.description:
Saccharine Biomes is a series of generative projects by Empress Trash that explore glitchy abstract aesthetics in generative tokens with different environments, flora and fauna in pretty super colorful pallets. These are created with both hand drawn elements and glitch photo collage to generate digital mixed media piece unique to each hash. 

7 Attributes total

8 - Backgrounds
6 - Sky Variations*
5 - Shiny Variations*
6 - Middlegrounds
6 - Foregrounds
6 - Foiliage Variations*
8 - Animals

Each Attribute has weighted rarities for fun times!
*includes 1 variation of none. 

All collage elements are CC0 and all tokens generated from this release are CC0.

metadata.name: Other ways #140
metadata.description:
Inspired by Paul Klee’s painting « Highways and byways », « Other ways » propose to build your own and unique generative painting.

7 features, including 4 main styles, 8 color palettes, 5 different parameters of the generative process.


Please note that the preview image is more saturated than the real token due to fxhash GPU management.

In Open Live window, press « s » to save the current image.
To get a High Resolution Image : press « r » to change the resolution for high definition, the image will reload and you can then use « s » to save the image (you can change DP in the URL to  a greater value for an even larger resolution in case you want to print it big).
This project is dimensionless, the Preview and OpenLive images are the same.

This artwork was created using p5js and scribble.

TidallyDisruptedStar. Paris. Jan 2022.

twitter : @TidallyD

metadata.name: Orbit Traps #123
metadata.description:
This is my first foray into generative NFTs. This is a variation of the Mandelbrot set. I first built a tool in Unity to find and record interesting locations of the set. Then I real-time render these parts inside of a shader and apply different orbit traps to the fractal. There is quite a bit of variation. Apart from different parts, and zoom levels, of the set, there are different orbit traps, symmetries, colors and animations (rare). I tried to balance the variety of images with the visual quality. This is a trade off because the more variety you allow for, the more likely it is that some of them will not look ideal. 

In the unlikely event you mint a completely black or white image, drop me a mail at countfrolic@gmail.com and I'll gladly mint you a new one.

Yours,
Martijn Steinrucken
The Art of Code

metadata.name: boxes_OUTLINED #94
notturno generativo #104
metadata.description:
by fabiello.art

my first generative nft is a nocturnal landscape written in p5.js, where I present my personal fusion of code and figurative art, a vision of hills and trees under a sky of stars and a full moon.
Each iteration presents a number of random variables such as to make the possible night scenarios tend to infinity, each capable of evoking different emotions due to its colors and shapes.

I like to imagine how every possible landscape is somehow connected to a physical or metaphysical place of the personal experience of the beholder. 
The use of the machine and the code, of human thought and its evolution up to our time, as an instrument of discovery and imaginative exploration of territories of the body and the soul.

The code of the trees is derived from J. Poliachik's Generative Trees.
1080x1080 px 
_
